criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  A call to the emergency medical assistance service;

          -  age> 18y,

          -  known time of stroke onset;

          -  transportation time from scene to the CSC longer than time to go to the nearest stroke
             unit or telemedicine hub;

          -  transportation time from scene to the CSC compatible with IV thrombolysis;

          -  known time from onset, RACE score ≥5.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  transportation time from scene to the CSC longer than time to go to the nearest stroke
             unit or telemedicine hub.

          -  no ambulance available

          -  bedridden patient
